docs.abstract: The chilling footage provides a new, up-close perspective on the last moments of Mr. Floyd’s life, as he screamed in terror, sobbed and pleaded with officers.

docs.lead_paragraph: Prosecutors showed chilling video from police body cameras as Derek Chauvin and other Minneapolis police officers confronted and tried to arrest George Floyd outside the Cup Foods in Minneapolis on May 25.

headline.main: ‘Don’t shoot me.’ Body camera video shows the fatal encounter between police officers and George Floyd.

docs.abstract: An independent report commissioned by the Los Angeles City Council faulted the department for its lack of planning and chaotic response.
docs.snippet: An independent report commissioned by the Los Angeles City Council faulted the department for its lack of planning and chaotic response.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Los Angeles Police Department severely mishandled protests last summer in the wake of George Floyd’s death, illegally detaining protesters, issuing conflicting orders to its rank-and-file officers and striking people who had committed no crimes with rubber bullets, bean bags and batons, according to a scathing report released on Thursday.

headline.main: L.A.P.D. Severely Mishandled George Floyd Protests, Report Finds
headline.print_headline: Los Angeles Police Exacerbated Chaos at Protests, Report Says

docs.abstract: On social media, on cable networks and even in the halls of Congress, supporters of Donald J. Trump tried to rewrite history in real time, pushing the fiction that left-wing agitators were to blame for the violence on Jan. 6.
docs.snippet: On social media, on cable networks and even in the halls of Congress, supporters of Donald J. Trump tried to rewrite history in real time, pushing the fiction that left-wing agitators were to blame for the violence on Jan. 6.
docs.lead_paragraph: At 1:51 p.m. on Jan. 6, a right-wing radio host named Michael D. Brown wrote on Twitter that rioters had breached the United States Capitol — and immediately speculated about who was really to blame. “Antifa or BLM or other insurgents could be doing it disguised as Trump supporters,” Mr. Brown wrote, using shorthand for Black Lives Matter. “Come on, man, have you never heard of psyops?”

headline.main: How Pro-Trump Forces Pushed a Lie About Antifa at the Capitol Riot
headline.print_headline: How a Lie Took Wing as the Capitol Riot Raged

docs.abstract: The firefighter, Genevieve Hansen, who is also an emergency medical technician, said police officers wouldn’t allow her to offer George Floyd assistance.
docs.snippet: The firefighter, Genevieve Hansen, who is also an emergency medical technician, said police officers wouldn’t allow her to offer George Floyd assistance.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Genevieve Hansen encountered police officers arresting George Floyd last May, she quickly realized that something was wrong. Ms. Hansen, who was off duty from her job as a Minneapolis firefighter and emergency medical technician, noticed that Mr. Floyd was handcuffed, seemed disoriented and that his face was “smushed into the ground,” she testified in court on Tuesday.

headline.main: An outspoken off-duty firefighter testified: ‘There was a man being killed.’

docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — A third-degree murder charge may be back on the table for Derek Chauvin, the former Minneapolis police officer charged in the death of George Floyd, after a ruling from the Minnesota Supreme Court on Wednesday.

headline.main: With Five Jurors Now Seated, Momentum Builds in Chauvin Trial
headline.print_headline: As Jury Fills, Chauvin Trial Nears Answer On Key Issue

docs.abstract: Derek Chauvin, 44, had been a police officer with the Minneapolis Police Department for more than 19 years before George Floyd’s death.
docs.snippet: Derek Chauvin, 44, had been a police officer with the Minneapolis Police Department for more than 19 years before George Floyd’s death.
docs.lead_paragraph: Derek Chauvin, 44, had been a police officer with the Minneapolis Police Department for more than 19 years before George Floyd’s death. During that time, he was the subject of at least 22 complaints and internal investigations. One of the episodes led to two letters of reprimand — his only formal discipline.

headline.main: What do we know about Derek Chauvin?
